N:skill-autoresearch
D:Improve an existing SKILL.md through a bounded eval-driven mutation loop with a frozen evaluator, one meaningful change at a time, explicit keep-or-revert decisions, and append-only experiment logs.
G:skill-autoresearch skill-optimization evals prompt-iteration benchmark mutation-loop ratcheting autoresearch

U[5]:
  Improve a reusable SKILL.md with measured iterations instead of ad hoc rewriting
  Freeze prompts and evals before mutating the skill
  Compare baseline versus mutations and keep only score-improving changes
  Add or refresh support files and discovery surfaces when the main boundary is proven
  Preserve append-only logs so future maintainers can reuse or reject prior mutations

S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,ConfirmInputs,Collect target skill path; 3-5 representative prompts; 3-6 binary evals; runs per experiment; budget cap; supporting files in scope
  2,ReadSkill,Read SKILL.md plus linked references; identify triggers; route-outs; failure modes; missing support coverage
  3,FreezeEvaluator,Write loop-charter.md with goal; baseline; mutable artifact; fixed harness; constraints; rejected directions
  4,Baseline,Create skill-autoresearch-[skill-name] artifacts and record experiment 0 on the fixed prompt set
  5,MutateLoop,Change one meaningful thing; rerun the same harness; keep only score improvements; revert ties or regressions
  6,SyncSupport,Update evals; compact variants; discovery manifests; docs/setup surfaces only if positioning changed materially
  7,Deliver,Report baseline-to-final score; keep-vs-revert count; top changes; remaining failures; artifact paths

R[7]:
  Do not start without target skill, representative prompts, and binary evals
  Freeze the evaluator before the first mutation
  Change one meaningful thing at a time so results stay attributable
  Keep or revert by measured score, not intuition
  Log every experiment, including reverts
  Treat hosted eval platforms as references, not substitutes for repo-local artifacts
  Start a new comparison track if prompts, evals, or scoring rules change

E[2]{desc,in,out}:
  "Trigger precision ratchet","Baseline a stale skill, rewrite the description only, and rerun the fixed eval suite","improved trigger precision without changing the evaluator; keep or revert decision logged"
  "Support-surface sync","After a justified main-skill improvement, update compact/discovery/docs surfaces that changed materially","support files and manifests synced after the core mutation proved out"
